I"ü<p>Firefox motion is quick, supportive and whimsical.</p>

<h2 id="-quick"><img src="../images/introduction/Quick.svg" alt="" /> Quick</h2>

<p>Animations should be fast and nimble, never keeping the user waiting longer than is necessary. The aim is to prioritize user-perceived performance over technical benchmarks.</p>

<h2 id="-supportive"><img src="../images/introduction/Supportive.svg" alt="" /> Supportive</h2>

<p>Motion should help ease the user through the experience. It should aid the flow of actions, giving clear guidance for user orientation: spatial or temporal.</p>

<h2 id="-whimsical"><img src="../images/introduction/Whimsical.svg" alt="" /> Whimsical</h2>

<p>Animations should have a playful and delightful personality when appropriate.</p>
